member.name: T:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass
member.summary: Types of species available in MinEql.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.None
member.summary: Represents an invalid class definition.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.SolubleComponent
member.summary: A soluble species which corresponds to the components.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.SolubleComplex
member.summary: Soluble species which is not a component.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.FixedSpecies
member.summary: Precipitated solids which are not allowed to dissolve.
member.remarks: These species may not disslve even if the amount of the species is negative. Examples are gases at a fixed partial pressure, or simply a solid phase which is specified to be present.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.DissolvablePrecipitatedSolid
member.summary: Precipitated solids which are subject to dissolution if the amount present becomes less than zero.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.PrecipitableSolid
member.summary: Dissolved solids which are subject to precipitation if the solubility product is exceeded.

member.name: F:Ecolab.Speciation.SpeciesClass.Ignore
member.summary: Species which are considered at all.
member.remarks: Examples are dissolved solids which are not permitted to precipitate, or the electron, which does not exist in solution.
